The paper discusses the development of a natural language query interface for searching personal information on smartwatches, which involves analyzing textual questions and constructing a text parser algorithm. This suggests that the paper may fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also likely sub-categories. The use of personal informatics and quantified-self data may also relate to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories.
